Pre-Game Insights: Gibraltar kick off their 2024 UEFA Nations League campaign against Liechtenstein at the Europa Sports Complex.
This will be the first meeting between the two nations since November 2022, when Gibraltar secured a 2-0 victory in a friendly.
Gibraltar picked up a morale-boosting result in their final warm-up game by beating Andorra 1-0 in a friendly.
Liechtenstein suffered a surprise 1-0 loss against San Marino in their Nations League group opener.
Gibraltar have lost their last 13 competitive matches, stretching back to a 1-1 draw against Bulgaria in June 2022.
Liechtenstein have gone 40 consecutive games without a win across all competitions, dating back to a 2-1 friendly victory over Luxembourg in October 2020.
Gibraltar boast a superior record in the history of this fixture with three wins from the last six meetings between the sides.
